    "caption": "Curved horns, impossible cliffs, and total confidence.",
    "shortDescription": "Ibex are wild mountain goats that walk on near-vertical cliff faces as casually as you'd stroll across a flat pavement. Their hooves have hard outer edges that grip rock and soft rubbery inner pads that grip smooth stone — essentially a built-in climbing shoe. Fun fact: Male ibex can grow curved horns over a metre long, and they use them to clash head-on in battles that can be heard echoing across whole valleys."
